      "amount": "To taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Red pepper flakes",
      "amount": "A pinch"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat a pan over medium heat and add water chestnuts. Cook for about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add onion and cook until translucent, approximately 3-4 minutes.",
    "Toss in garlic and bell peppers; stir-fry for about 5 more minutes.",
    "Pour in tomato sauce, soy sauce, apple cider vinegar, and a pinch of salt. Stir well to combine all ingredients.",
    "Lower heat to low-medium and simmer for another 5 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Add water chestnuts back into the pan. Give it a last stir before serving.",
    "Finish with chopped cilantro on top if desired."
  ],
